<@U056YJVMJ14> If you were wanting to share data from your local database, when your database is not accessible other than locally, you could always export the data from your tables into a CSV and send to your teammate so they can use your same test data by importing it.

I think in a lot of real world situations though, the database will either be accessible in a private network or even publicly through authorized connections.

elements.text:
If you were wanting to share data from your local database, when your database is not accessible other than locally, you could always export the data from your tables into a CSV and send to your teammate so they can use your same test data by importing it.

I think in a lot of real world situations though, the database will either be accessible in a private network or even publicly through authorized connections.
